   <express_ref linkend="part_collection:arm:Part_collection_arm"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
	<ext_description linkend="Part_collection_arm"/>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Part_collection_arm  Entity: Collected_item_association  
   <express_ref linkend="part_collection:arm:Part_collection_arm.Collected_item_association"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Part_collection_arm.Collected_item_association">
A <b>Collected_item_association</b> is a mechanism to associate <express_ref linkend="product_occurrence:arm:Product_occurrence_arm.Product_occurrence"/> instances with a <express_ref linkend="part_collection:arm:Part_collection_arm.Collection_definition"/>.

A <express_ref linkend="part_collection:arm:Part_collection_arm.Collected_item_association"/> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_occurrence:arm:Product_occurrence_arm.Part_occurrence_definition_relationship"/>.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Part_collection_arm  Entity: Collected_item_association  Attribute: relating_view 
   <express_ref linkend="part_collection:arm:Part_collection_arm.Collected_item_association.relating_view"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Part_collection_arm.Collected_item_association.relating_view">
the <b>relating_view</b> specifies the <express_ref linkend="part_collection:arm:Part_collection_arm.Collection_definition"/> that collects the <express_ref linkend="product_occurrence:arm:Product_occurrence_arm.Product_occurrence"/> instances.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Part_collection_arm  Entity: Collected_item_association  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="part_collection:arm:Part_collection_arm.Collected_item_association.wr:WR1"/>
	   
		 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Part_collection_arm.Collected_item_association.wr:WR1">
there are not <express_ref linkend="assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Assembly_component_relationship"/> instances.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Part_collection_arm  Entity: Collection_definition  
   <express_ref linkend="part_collection:arm:Part_collection_arm.Collection_definition"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Part_collection_arm.Collection_definition">
A <b>Collection_definition</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="part_view_definition:arm:Part_view_definition_arm.Part_view_definition"/> that identifies a collection of parts that are mounted in the same product but may not be assembled together.
<p>Members of the collection are specified with instances of <express_ref linkend="part_collection:arm:Part_collection_arm.Collected_item_association"/>.
</p>
		<example>Windscreen wipers for a car or a set of kitchen tools, offered as an option of a kitchen top, are examples of collection.</example>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Part_collection_arm  Entity: Collection_definition  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="part_collection:arm:Part_collection_arm.Collection_definition.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Part_collection_arm.Collection_definition.wr:WR1">
the "Part collection" shall be a definition of a version of a product of type 'collection'
</ext_description>
